4
00:00:09.300 --> 00:00:12.400
Okay. So this presentation, just to give you the stage,

5
00:00:13.780 --> 00:00:16.939
will focus on the interaction between cancer cell and the

6
00:00:17.040 --> 00:00:20.420
microenvironment, and this interaction at the local level are very important.

7
00:00:20.480 --> 00:00:24.060
These will allow the tumor to grow and to evolve, and of course, also to

8
00:00:24.100 --> 00:00:27.940
metastasize. But during metastasis, cancer cell will have to adapt to

9
00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:29.080
each of the very different

10
00:00:31.220 --> 00:00:34.720
organ that will metastasize. And what we will

11
00:00:34.780 --> 00:00:38.360
particularly pay attention here is actually the systemic

12
00:00:38.380 --> 00:00:41.860
interaction, rather than the local one, that the tumor will

13
00:00:41.920 --> 00:00:43.589
establish with the rest of the body,

14
00:00:44.420 --> 00:00:48.060
which will, in some way, facilitate the adaptation

15
00:00:48.800 --> 00:00:50.200
of the tumor

16
00:00:51.060 --> 00:00:54.780
at the metastatic site. So this is very complicated image, but it's

17
00:00:54.880 --> 00:00:58.840
just to show you how different are the different metastatic niches

18
00:00:58.940 --> 00:01:00.800
between the different organ. And in

19
00:01:02.160 --> 00:01:06.130
this session, we will mainly look at adaptation mechanism between bone and

20
00:01:06.740 --> 00:01:10.600
brain. And of course, we will look at the systemic changes which will

21
00:01:10.660 --> 00:01:14.460
facilitate this adaptation, and also reflect on the fact that those changes

22
00:01:14.500 --> 00:01:16.920
change the physiology of the organism as a whole.

23
00:01:17.600 --> 00:01:21.540
So before further ado, I'm going to start by introducing our first

24
00:01:21.550 --> 00:01:22.420
speaker, which is

25
00:01:23.420 --> 00:01:25.730
Yibin Kang from Princeton. Please come

26
00:01:26.680 --> 00:01:30.620
to the stage. And, okay, and

27
