600
00:35:18.616 --> 00:35:21.496
And talk about pre-metastatic niche.

601
00:35:22.316 --> 00:35:26.036
Dr. Kang already touched on Dr. Paget's

602
00:35:26.636 --> 00:35:29.036
seed and soil hypothesis. Basically,

603
00:35:29.856 --> 00:35:33.396
back in 1889, he

604
00:35:34.096 --> 00:35:37.296
described the distribution of the

605
00:35:37.356 --> 00:35:38.736
secondary growth

606
00:35:40.036 --> 00:35:43.976
in cancers of the breast. And he found

607
00:35:44.036 --> 00:35:47.436
this non-random pattern of metastasis,

608
00:35:48.096 --> 00:35:51.116
and asked, "What is it that

609
00:35:53.496 --> 00:35:56.696
decides what organs still suffer

610
00:35:57.576 --> 00:36:01.256
in a case of disseminated cancer?"

611
00:36:01.956 --> 00:36:05.496
And based on his observation, he

612
00:36:05.556 --> 00:36:09.416
proposed that the remote organ cannot be

613
00:36:09.456 --> 00:36:13.236
altogether passive or indifferent

614
00:36:13.316 --> 00:36:16.596
as regards to embolism. So this is the initial

615
00:36:17.196 --> 00:36:21.056
seed and soil hypothesis. And

616
00:36:21.096 --> 00:36:24.936
then in 2003, Dr. Fiddler from

617
00:36:24.976 --> 00:36:28.436
my institution revisit this hypothesis,

618
00:36:29.156 --> 00:36:33.100
clearly indicate that some tumor cellsMeaning the

619
00:36:33.240 --> 00:36:36.920
seed grew preferentially in a microenvironment

620
00:36:37.320 --> 00:36:40.980
of selected organs, the soil. And metastasis

621
00:36:41.480 --> 00:36:45.240
resulted only when the appropriate seed was

622
00:36:45.320 --> 00:36:48.760
implanted in its suitable soil, like this one.

623
00:36:49.560 --> 00:36:51.340
So the suitable soil

624
00:36:52.540 --> 00:36:55.580
now in scientific term is what we meant

625
00:36:57.580 --> 00:37:00.900
metastasis niche, a nutritive and supportive

626
00:37:00.960 --> 00:37:04.800
microenvironment for disseminating tumor cells to

627
00:37:04.860 --> 00:37:08.500
survive, colonize, and grow in distant organ

628
00:37:08.620 --> 00:37:12.600
sites. And now this

629
00:37:12.700 --> 00:37:16.530
led us to this new concept of pre-metastatic

630
00:37:16.600 --> 00:37:20.400
niche, which is beyond Dr. Page's

631
00:37:20.480 --> 00:37:24.060
original hypothesis. I call it seed and soil 2.0.

632
00:37:24.860 --> 00:37:28.100
What is a PMN? Well,

633
00:37:28.880 --> 00:37:32.480
it's a receptive microenvironment in a distant organ

634
00:37:32.960 --> 00:37:36.520
established, pay attention here, prior to the

635
00:37:36.619 --> 00:37:40.180
arrival of cancer cells. Basically, primary tumors

636
00:37:40.600 --> 00:37:43.800
can initiate a chronic systemic state,

637
00:37:44.300 --> 00:37:48.240
gradually ripening distant organs to make them

638
00:37:48.280 --> 00:37:51.900
become friendly, hospitable for disseminated

639
00:37:52.340 --> 00:37:53.480
circulating tumor cells.

640
00:37:54.460 --> 00:37:57.220
And the PMN

641
00:37:57.780 --> 00:38:00.640
actually is not a static

642
00:38:01.340 --> 00:38:04.660
landscape. It's a chronologically evolving

643
00:38:05.080 --> 00:38:06.100
systemic state.

644
00:38:07.420 --> 00:38:10.800
Represents the transition from a local

645
00:38:10.960 --> 00:38:14.320
malignancy primary tumor to a system disease

646
00:38:15.260 --> 00:38:17.100
metastasis to multiple organ sites.

647
00:38:18.180 --> 00:38:18.480
And

648
00:38:19.300 --> 00:38:23.060
talking about this chronologically evolving system state,

649
00:38:23.820 --> 00:38:25.120
at least there are three

650
00:38:26.300 --> 00:38:26.700
stages.

651
00:38:27.760 --> 00:38:30.800
The early stage, we call the initiation of systemic

652
00:38:30.920 --> 00:38:34.640
conditioning. Basically, right after

653
00:38:34.650 --> 00:38:36.350
primary tumor formation,

654
00:38:37.360 --> 00:38:41.340
and those tumor-secreted exosomes or factors

655
00:38:41.400 --> 00:38:45.180
can get into a circulation to induce immune

656
00:38:45.280 --> 00:38:48.680
suppression or remodeling extracellular matrix.

657
00:38:49.820 --> 00:38:51.220
And the middle stage

658
00:38:52.300 --> 00:38:56.280
more involve myeloid recruitment, and

659
00:38:56.740 --> 00:39:00.240
it's a state of chronic inflammation to

660
00:39:00.340 --> 00:39:03.000
license tumor cells for colonization.

661
00:39:03.680 --> 00:39:03.820
And

662
00:39:04.900 --> 00:39:07.520
one of the major change is recruitment of

663
00:39:08.240 --> 00:39:12.000
myeloid-derived suppressor cells from bone

664
00:39:12.060 --> 00:39:12.360
marrow.

665
00:39:13.440 --> 00:39:16.820
The late stage involve in multiple

666
00:39:16.900 --> 00:39:17.740
alterations,

667
00:39:18.580 --> 00:39:22.360
and here are at least some of them: angiogenesis, immune

668
00:39:22.480 --> 00:39:24.990
evasion, metabolic dysregulation,

669
00:39:25.800 --> 00:39:29.120
neuroinvasion, which is relatively new

670
00:39:29.220 --> 00:39:30.220
frontier

671
00:39:31.120 --> 00:39:34.400
in term of PMN. And all these change can

672
00:39:34.560 --> 00:39:37.780
favor disseminated tumor cells to outgrow

673
00:39:38.800 --> 00:39:40.620
in the secondary organ site.

674
00:39:41.600 --> 00:39:43.680
And here I use this cartoon to

675
00:39:44.520 --> 00:39:48.400
reiterate the key steps. Basically, primary

676
00:39:48.440 --> 00:39:52.330
tumors secrete exosomes of different factors

677
00:39:52.820 --> 00:39:56.280
that enter the circulation, travel to different organ

678
00:39:56.440 --> 00:40:00.330
sites. And once they are in these organ sites, they

679
00:40:00.440 --> 00:40:04.200
can induce ECM remodeling or induce

680
00:40:04.280 --> 00:40:07.760
immune suppression or angiogenesis to

681
00:40:07.820 --> 00:40:11.040
establish the pre-metastatic niche to help

682
00:40:12.640 --> 00:40:15.920
future arriving metastatic tumor cell to outgrow.

683
00:40:16.960 --> 00:40:17.160
Well,

684
00:40:19.520 --> 00:40:20.620
you can see

685
00:40:21.420 --> 00:40:25.040
pre-metastatic niche in different organ sites are very different.

686
00:40:25.560 --> 00:40:25.700
So

687
00:40:26.860 --> 00:40:30.660
how tumors select the right environment for them to

688
00:40:30.720 --> 00:40:31.080
future

689
00:40:31.880 --> 00:40:35.320
metastasize to. So this brings to the concept,

690
00:40:35.580 --> 00:40:38.670
the deep code of metastasis. And Dr.

691
00:40:38.880 --> 00:40:41.470
David Lyden's team is really

692
00:40:42.440 --> 00:40:46.000
a pioneer group, made a lot of important

693
00:40:46.060 --> 00:40:47.620
discoveries. And

694
00:40:49.660 --> 00:40:53.120
basically, the key message is that they found

695
00:40:53.560 --> 00:40:57.060
tumor-secreted extracellular vehicles or

696
00:40:57.400 --> 00:41:00.600
extracellular particles. They contain different

697
00:41:00.680 --> 00:41:04.000
biomolecules on these

698
00:41:04.060 --> 00:41:07.840
EVPs, and those biomolecules can

699
00:41:08.120 --> 00:41:11.970
guide or determine where the tumor cell will

700
00:41:12.040 --> 00:41:14.620
metastasize to. And they have

701
00:41:15.360 --> 00:41:18.820
identified all these different

702
00:41:18.880 --> 00:41:22.780
molecules guide tumor cell metastasis to all

703
00:41:22.800 --> 00:41:25.740
these different organ sites. I'm not going to

704
00:41:26.700 --> 00:41:30.320
discuss them one by one, but I do want to highlight

705
00:41:30.660 --> 00:41:32.600
this one, CEACAM1/MIP.

706
00:41:34.140 --> 00:41:37.700
What they found is that when tumor-secreted

707
00:41:38.000 --> 00:41:40.640
extracellular vehicles express this

708
00:41:41.300 --> 00:41:42.280
CEACAM1/MIP,

709
00:41:43.120 --> 00:41:46.940
they will guide the tumor cell to metastasize to the

710
00:41:46.980 --> 00:41:50.820
brain. And they also found that this

711
00:41:51.080 --> 00:41:54.830
biomolecule can serve as a biomarker and

712
00:41:54.960 --> 00:41:56.000
therapeutic targets

713
00:41:57.140 --> 00:41:58.360
for brain metastasis.

714
00:41:59.320 --> 00:42:03.240
And along that line, I like to deep dive

715
00:42:03.580 --> 00:42:06.920
into the unique architecture of the

716
00:42:07.360 --> 00:42:08.800
brain pre-metastatic niche.

717
00:42:09.760 --> 00:42:13.260
Why I focus on this, well, I'm sure

718
00:42:13.740 --> 00:42:17.680
you'll all agree that brain metastasis is really an

719
00:42:17.760 --> 00:42:21.360
imposing clinical challenge, and the instance

